.TH "CUSTOMELEMENTREGISTRY.GET" "3JS" "December 1, 2025" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
CustomElementRegistry.get \- CustomElementRegistry: get() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]get()\f[B]\f[R] method of the
\f[CR]CustomElementRegistry\f[R] interface returns the constructor for a
previously\-defined custom element.
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
get(name)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]name\f[R]
The name of the custom element.
.SS Return value
The constructor for the named custom element, or \f[CR]undefined\f[R] if
there is no custom element defined with the name.
.SH EXAMPLES
.IP
.EX
customElements.define(
  \(dqmy\-paragraph\(dq,
  \f[B]class\f[R] \f[B]extends\f[R] HTMLElement {
    constructor() {
      \f[B]const\f[R] template = document.getElementById(\(dqcustom\-paragraph\(dq);
      \f[B]super\f[R]() \f[I]// returns element this scope\f[R]
        .attachShadow({ mode: \(dqopen\(dq }) \f[I]// sets AND returns this.shadowRoot\f[R]
        .append(document.importNode(template.content, \f[B]true\f[R]));
    }
  },
);

\f[I]// Return a reference to the my\-paragraph constructor\f[R]
\f[B]const\f[R] ctor = customElements.get(\(dqmy\-paragraph\(dq);
.EE
